title: Review ties with Pyongyang, BN Youth urges gov't
text:
More 
BN Youth has urged the Malaysian government to review its ties with North Korea in the wake of diplomatic friction between Putrajaya and Pyongyang over the murder of Kim Jong-nam. 
Umno Youth vice-chief Khairul Azwan Harun made the call after a leading a protest outside the North Korean embassy in Kuala Lumpur this evening, which saw participants brandishing placards which stated “Respect Malaysia”, and other messages on a more satirical note.
